column168: DRIVER MAKING DELIVERY ON CITY ROUTES SMELLED ACID FUMES IN TRAILER. HE LOOKED AND DISCOVERED A 5-GALLON CONTAINER OF PRECLEANER (NOT KNOWN AS HYDR OCHLORIC ACID AT TIME) LEAKING INTO THE TRAILER. DRIVER TOOK FREIGHT TO CON SIGNEE WHO RECEIVED DAMAGED FREIGHT. DRIVER HAD DELIVERED OTHER FREIGHT TO LOCATION WHERE INJURIES OCCURED, AT ALPINE SKI. DRIVER EXPLAINED TO RECEIVI NG CLERKS AT ALPINE THAT THERE WAS AN ACID SUBSTANCE ON TWO OF THE SEVEN BOXES BEING DELIVERED AND ADVISED RECEIVING TO TAKE CARE. ONE CLERK TOUCHED HER MOUTH AFTER CLEANING HER HANDS, BUT HAD ACID RESIDUE UNDER FINGERNAIL WHICH RESULTED IN MINOR BURN ON LIP. THE SECOND CLERK INHALED FUMES WHEN THROWING AWAY CARDBORD WITH ACID RESIDUE, CAUSED BY A GUST OF WIND. HE RECEIVED A MINOR LUNG IRRITATION. IN FUTURE CONTAMINATED FREIGHT SHOULD NOT BE DELIVERED. ALSO PROPER SHIPPING NAMES AND DESCRIPTIONS FOR HAZMAT SHOULD BE VERIFIED BEFORE HANDLING FREIGHT.
